{
  "text": "In the present study, stable MI patients showed decreased hsCRP levels. This could be because all stable MI patients were on standard medication which included Statin which not only reduces cholesterol level but also has an anti-inflammatory activity. This is in accordance with Nissen et al. [CITATION_1] who have hypothesized & showed that Statins bring down CRP level and reduce the risk of coronary heart disease.",
